[2026-03-09T01:12:50Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TuSf18xng2guXJP3Nziwr9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile my findings into a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found a comprehensive set of code related to displaying project info with expandable prompts sections. Here's what I discovered:\n\n### 1. **Backend API Handlers** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`)\n\n**Project Info Handler (lines 939-1025):**\n- `handleAPIProjectInfo()` - Fetches project metadata including:\n  - Docker image (parsed from Dockerfile)\n  - Version number (from `.cloche/version`)\n  - **Prompt files history** - Executes `git log --follow` for each prompt file to retrieve commit history with SHA, date, and message\n\n**Prompt Diff Handler (lines 1027-1056):**\n- `handleAPIPromptDiff()` - Retrieves git diff for a specific commit of a prompt file\n  - Takes `file` and `sha` query parameters\n  - Executes `git diff sha^..sha -- file` to show what changed in that commit\n  - Validates SHA to prevent injection attacks\n\n**Related Workflow Handler (lines 1058-1132):**\n- `handleAPIWorkflows()` - Lists all workflow definitions with step details\n- `handleAPIStepContent()` - Fetches step configuration and prompt/script file contents\n\n### 2. **Frontend Template & JavaScript** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`)\n\n**Project Info Panel (lines 25-29):**\n- Renders a panel titled \"Project Info\" with the content loaded via API\n\n**JavaScript Functions:**\n\n**loadProjectInfo() (lines 89-121):**\n- Fetches project info from `/api/projects/{name}/info`\n- Builds HTML with Docker image, version, and prompt files section\n- Uses HTML `<details>/<summary>` elements for expandable sections\n- Creates `<div class=\"prompt-commit\">` elements for each commit in history\n- Each commit shows: SHA (short), date, message, and is clickable\n\n**toggleDiff() (lines 123-139):**\n- Handles click on a prompt commit entry\n- Checks if diff is already shown (remove if exists - toggle behavior)\n- Otherwise fetches diff via `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=...&sha=...`\n- Creates `<pre class=\"diff-block\">` element with the diff output\n- Inserts the diff block after the commit row\n\n**HTML Structure for Prompts:**\n```html\n<details>\n  <summary class=\"mono\">path/to/prompt.md</summary>\n  <div class=\"prompt-commit\" data-file=\"...\" data-sha=\"...\" onclick=\"toggleDiff(this)\">\n    <!-- commit info -->\n  </div>\n  <!-- toggleDiff inserts <pre class=\"diff-block\"> here -->\n</details>\n```\n\n### 3. **CSS Styling** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`)\n\n**Details/Summary Styling (lines 197-221):**\n- `details` element: basic margin styling\n- `details summary`: cursor pointer, font-weight 600, muted color\n- Native browser disclosure triangle (no custom arrow needed)\n\n**Diff Block Styling (lines 550-563):**\n- `.diff-block`: monospace font, light background, scrollable container\n- Styled to display git diff output nicely\n\n### 4. **API Routing** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` lines 139-157)\n\nRoutes configured:\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/info` → `handleAPIProjectInfo`\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` → `handleAPIPromptDiff`\n- `GET /projects/{name}` → `handleProjectDetail` (HTML page)\n\n### 5. **gRPC Server** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n\nThe gRPC server handles:\n- Run orchestration and workflow execution\n- Log streaming and step execution tracking\n- Container lifecycle management\n- No direct project info endpoint (HTTP/web only)\n\n---\n\n### **Key Technical Details:**\n\n**Expansion Mechanism:**\n- Uses native HTML `<details>/<summary>` elements (browser-native disclosure widgets with automatic triangles)\n- No custom arrow icons needed - browser provides default disclosure triangle\n- Toggling is handled both by browser (summary clicks) and custom JS (commit diffs)\n\n**Git Integration:**\n- Prompt files history retrieved via: `git log --follow --format=%H %aI %s -- .cloche/prompts/file.md`\n- Diffs generated via: `git diff sha^..sha -- file`\n- Both commands run in the project directory with proper path handling\n\n**File Content vs Git Commits:**\n- File contents are loaded per-step via `handleAPIStepContent()`\n- Commit history and diffs are retrieved via git commands\n- No direct file reading for prompt display - all through git history\n\n---\n\n### **File Paths:**\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Backend API handlers\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Frontend template with JavaScript\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - CSS styling\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC server (no project info endpoint)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2d780a1854ac66c6 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63961\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 30081</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b2e4882-efc4-451e-8682-2b6d417f2e4d","uuid":"3fac2fd3-d4bf-41de-b8fe-4c593bda3412","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find code related to displaying project info, especially the \"Prompts\" section with expansion arrows. Look for:\n1. Any UI/TUI code that shows project info pages\n2. Code that handles expanding/collapsing prompts sections\n3. Code that reads prompt file contents vs git commits\n4. Any gRPC or CLI handler for project info/details\n\nSearch broadly across the codebase - check cmd/, internal/, and any UI-related directories. Look for keywords like \"prompt\", \"expand\", \"project info\", \"detail\", \"collapse\", \"arrow\", \"file contents\", \"git log\", \"commit\". Be very thorough.","agentId":"a2d780a1854ac66c6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information I need.